expectvalue /Class
doit
PythonInstance comment:
'Common base class for Python user classes generated by ClassDefAst.

Phase B: every Python instance attribute lives in GemStone dynamic
instance variable storage (``Object>>dynamicInstVarAt:put:'').
ClassDefAst no longer pre-declares static instVars or synthesizes
accessor/setter pairs — assignments like ``self.x = y'' compile
directly to ``self @env0:dynamicInstVarAt: #x put: y'', and reads
compile to ``(self @env0:dynamicInstVarAt: #x ifAbsent: [self
@env1:___pyAttrLoad___: #x])'' so a missing instance attribute falls
through to class-method lookup.

The DNU handler below covers Smalltalk-style sends that bypass
codegen — ``obj name:'' (1-arg) writes via dynamicInstVarAt:put:,
``obj name'' (0-arg) reads via dynamicInstVarAt:.  Subclasses with
varargs forwarders (``_name:kw:'') still route through the explicit
selector first.'
%

expectvalue /Class
doit
PythonInstance category: 'Modules'
%

! ------------------- Remove existing behavior
removeallmethods PythonInstance
